  <scopecontent id="aspace_672d3925b59035e32c6aa423c7f20d80">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The collection consists of legal documents relating to property and estates in the Town of Bushwick during the 18th and 19th centuries. The bulk of documents relate to the Skillman family. Other families represented in the collection include the Church, Conselyea, Misserol (or Miserol/Miserool/Meserole), and Woortman (or Woertman) familes. The collection includes a document listing awards granted for the widening of North 2nd St., in Williamsburg, Brooklyn. It also includes a 1932 lease to the Riggs family for property in East Orange, NJ.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_356c5ccb81e57db6129ea80daa5c0c1f">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>Documents have been grouped together by family by the processing archivist. Folders are arranged alphabetically.</p>  </arrangement>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_d7a362f5344488a3555015c68022ecaa">
    <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
<p>Open to users without restrictions.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_fdae8b4f5dcc5168cf6f445867debf58">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Gift of Ruth Riggs Smith, 2006. The collection had belonged to her father, Charles Church Riggs, whose family originally collected the documents.</p>  </acqinfo>
